    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 18 October 1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">The bearer of the letter did not wait for him to send a
                            letter when they received news that the new Pope has been elected: it is
                            Cardinal Alessandro Farnese. Lodovico Gritti is rumoured to have been
                            killed by his Romanian (Dacian) compatriots from Transylvania. If only
                            they knew what the Sultan was planning regarding the Hungarian affairs;
                            the French, the Veneti, and the Pope only know some details. Cristoforo
                            Doria has gone to Syria with two boats and occupied Tyre, then he went
                            over to Palestine; it is known exactly how big a devastation he has
                            inflicted on the Turkish forces. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Camillus Gilinus Nicolao Olao suo salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Commodum tabellarius recesserat, cum nobis allatum fuit cardinalem
                        <persName>Farnesium</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Alessandro
                        Farnese (1468–1549) was elected on 13 October, 1534 and became Pope Paul
                        III. On the election see Ghilino’s previous letter: Ep.
                            514.<ref>olahus.tei.15341012_2</ref></note> pontificem designatum esse,
                    omniaque <placeName>Romae</placeName> pacata. Fama nos tenet
                        <persName>Griteum</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Lodovico
                        Gritti was killed on 29 September, 1534.</note> Turcae a Dacis tuis civibus
                    interfectum. </p>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Utinam prius caesaris Turcarum sententiam super rebus Hungaricis
                    perscrutati essent, multa certe ex eo de Gallis et fortasse de Venetis et
                    pontifice ad rem nostram cognovissent, sed Deus optimus maximus operam dabit, ut
                    aequi et iniqui intelligant, caesarum nostrorum <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >illustrissimarum</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr"
                        >illustrissimam</add> domum sibi oppido curae esse. <persName>Christophorus
                        Auria</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.3">Cristoforo
                        Doria.</note><persName>principis Auriae</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">Andrea Doria.</note> nepos ex sorore, qui pyraticam
                    faciebat, in <placeName>Syriam</placeName> cum duabus actuariis navibus
                    descendit et capta <placeName>Tyro</placeName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.5">Tyre.</note> depopulata et incensa transmittebat in
                    Palestinam, certum habemus illum in hac expeditione IIII triremes et fustes V <choice>
                        <orig>Turcis</orig>
                        <supplied>Turcos</supplied>
                    </choice> intercepisse, et magnis divitiis auctum. Vale et me <persName>Virgini
                        Lucretiae</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6"> Lucretia Caballis
                        (vom Ross).</note> plurimum commenda. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XV. Kalendas Novembris anno Domini
                    1534.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
